    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>Using the sketch of the function \(f(x) = {@f@}\) below, confirm that there is a simple root near \(x_0 = {@x0@}\).</p>
<figure class="HELM_figure">
    [[jsxgraph]]
    const brd = JXG.JSXGraph.initBoard(divid, {boundingbox: [-1, 5, 6, -5], axis: true, showCopyright: false});
    const f = brd.jc.snippet('{#f#}', true, 'x', true);
    const plot = brd.create('functiongraph', [f]);
    [[/jsxgraph]]
</figure>
<p>Use two iterations of the Newtonâ€“Raphson method to obtain a better estimate of the root.</p>
<p>Keep track of the values of \(x_1\) and \(x_2\), and give them here to \(4\) d.p.</p>
<p>\(x_1 = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>
<p>\(x_2 = \) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>First we find the derivative of \(f\), which is given by</p>
\[f'(x) = {@df@}.\]
<p>Next, we repeatedly apply the formula:</p>
\[x_{n+1} = x_n - \frac{f(x_n)}{f'(x_n)}\]
<p>With \(x_0 = {@x0@}\), we get</p>
\[x_1 = {@x0@} - \frac{{@decimalplaces(subst(x0, x, f), 4)@}}{{@decimalplaces(subst(x0, x, df), 4)@}} = {@ta1@}, \quad \text{to 4 d.p.}\]
<p>With \(x_1 = {@x1@}\), we get</p>
\[x_2 = {@x1@} - \frac{{@decimalplaces(subst(x1, x, f), 4)@}}{{@decimalplaces(subst(x1, x, df), 4)@}} = {@ta2@}, \quad \text{to 4 d.p.}\]
<p>We can visualise the process in the following graph.</p>
[[jsxgraph]]
const brd = JXG.JSXGraph.initBoard(divid, {boundingbox: [1.5, 2, 3.5, -4], axis: true, showCopyright: false});
const f = brd.jc.snippet('{#f#}', true, 'x', true);
const plot = brd.create('functiongraph', [f]);
const x0 = brd.create('point', [{#x0#}, 0], {name: 'x_0', fixed: true});
const y0 = brd.create('point', [function() {return x0.X();}, function() {return f(x0.X());}],
    {withLabel: false, size: 2, strokeColor: 'none'});
const auxl0 = brd.create('line', [x0, y0], {dash: 2, strokeColor: 'red', straightFirst: false, straightLast: false});
const x1 = brd.create('point', [{#x1#}, 0], {name: 'x_1', fixed: true});
const l1 = brd.create('line', [y0, x1], {strokeColor: 'green'});
const y1 = brd.create('point', [function() {return x1.X();}, function() {return f(x1.X());}],
    {withLabel: false, size: 2, strokeColor: 'none'});
const auxl1 = brd.create('line', [x1, y1], {dash: 2, strokeColor: 'red', straightFirst: false, straightLast: false});
const x2 = brd.create('point', [{#x2#}, 0], {name: 'x_2', fixed: true, strokeColor: 'green', fillColor: 'green'});
const l2 = brd.create('line', [y1, x2], {strokeColor: 'green'});
[[/jsxgraph]]]]></text>
